📊 Dataset Information

The dataset used in this project is publicly available:

US Accidents Dataset (Kaggle)
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/sobhanmoosavi/us-accidents

This dataset contains 7+ million accident records across the United States, including:

Location details (state, city, coordinates)
Weather conditions
Time of accident
Severity level
Road and traffic conditions

⚠️ Note: The dataset is not included in this repository due to its large size. It must be downloaded separately from Kaggle.

☁️ Cloud Architecture (AWS Services Used)

This project is built using a serverless AWS Big Data architecture:

Amazon S3 → Data storage (Raw + Processed data)
Amazon EC2 → Dataset ingestion from Kaggle
AWS Glue → ETL processing & data transformation
AWS Glue Data Catalog → Metadata management
Amazon Athena → SQL-based data analysis
Amazon QuickSight → Data visualization dashboard
Amazon CloudWatch → Monitoring & logs
IAM Roles → Secure access management
⚙️ Project Workflow
Dataset downloaded from Kaggle using EC2
Raw data stored in Amazon S3 (raw/)
AWS Glue Crawler detects schema and creates metadata
AWS Glue ETL job cleans and transforms data
Processed data stored in Parquet format (processed/)
Athena used for SQL-based analysis
QuickSight dashboard created for visualization
Machine learning model applied for accident severity prediction
